-- Ukraine’s Astarta Gets IFC Loan for Soybean, Biogas Facilities
-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 2012-11-06T16:44:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-06/ukraine-s-astarta-gets-ifc-loan-for-soybean-biogas-facilities.html
Ukrainian agriculture company  Astarta
Holding N.V. (AST)  signed a financing agreement of as much as $40
million with the World Bank’s International Financial
Corporation.  The loan is to be used for a soybean crushing plant,
construction of a biogas facility and the expansion of
agricultural land as well as infrastructure projects aimed at
increasing production, the company, based in the capital Kiev,
said in a regulatory statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  